This paper deals with the universal approximation property of neural networks, which is a fundamental concept in the field of neural networks and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on two-hidden-layer feedforward networks, which are commonly used in practical applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, the paper also involves approximation of continuous functions, which is related to topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI).
